{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Deep learning models, such as convolutional neural networks (CNNs) (O'Shea & Nash, 2015) and recurrent neural networks (RNNs) (Salehinejad et al., 2017), have become increasingly popular in recent years due to their ability to capture complex patterns in language data (Cho, et al., 2014; Peters, Neumann et al., 2018).",
    "Recently, the Transformer architecture introduced by Vaswani et al., 2017, has become the standard for pre-training large-scale language models, with a different approach from RNN models (Raffel, et al., 2020).",
    "RNNs process input data sequentially and maintain a hidden state that captures information from the previous inputs.",
    "This hidden state is passed to the next time step and updated based on the current input, allowing the model to capture temporal dependencies in the input sequence.",
    "Transformers, on the other hand, use an attention mechanism to directly model the relationships between all input positions, rather than processing them sequentially (Dai, et al., 2019)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Deep learning models, such as convolutional neural networks (CNNs) (O'Shea & Nash, 2015) and recurrent neural networks (RNNs) (Salehinejad et al., 2017), have become increasingly popular in recent years due to their ability to capture complex patterns in language data (Cho, et al., 2014; Peters, Neumann et al., 2018).",
    "Recently, the Transformer architecture introduced by Vaswani et al., 2017, has become the standard for pre-training large-scale language models, with a different approach from RNN models (Raffel, et al., 2020).",
    "Transformers, on the other hand, use an attention mechanism to directly model the relationships between all input positions, rather than processing them sequentially (Dai, et al., 2019)."
  ]
}